I don't have the epic weapon (though I'm so close it's miserable... WTB Crown/Earthstaff on Quellious!)<br>
I do have many of my spells, but I don't have T-Rod or Muzzle.  <br>
Setup:  Air pet, give him 2 lev rings, set of plate, 1 coldstone, and 2 swords (because I have gloves of bladecalling and I can, dammit!)<br>
<br>
****STOP SKIPPING****<br>
Now the important stuff:  At 56, soloing this guy is about the same xp I get soloing the front 6 in the hole.  Yes, the hole is light blue, and yes you're 'never' supposed to do light blues for xp because they suck.  But the fact is, with the set up outlined above, I find myself spending around 500 mana per kill in the hole.  It's easy:  Cancel to pull.  Sic pet.  Wait till they're at the &quot;m&quot; in &quot;an elemental warrior&quot; and throw a shock of swords.  This kills them or gets them low enough for the pet to kill them before they take more than a few steps in wander mode.  Heal the pet with 52 pet heal.  Repeat.  Doing this, mana cost is just about zero, I finish the 6-cycle around 60-70% with no clarity of any kind, nor t-rods, nor any FT items.<br>
<br>
Now Dapper:  at 56, with the pet set up as above, I throw 5 chars and he's dead.  I don't know what the problem that others are having is, but with JBoots, just char him until he's on you, then run till the pet gets him off, then char again... 5 full or nearly full damage chars, and the 53 air pet with cadeau/BOIII can kill him every time.  Pull with malosini, and if he partial resists, maybe add another char depending on how the pet is doing.<br>
<br>
Conclusion:  In the hole, I spend about half of the spawn cycle waiting on the damn things to pop.  If I had a way to pull the 'next 2' that spawn in ambush mode down the stairs, I'd do it, and the hole would be a-number-one for experience.  I group often here with some of my friends, usually a mix of 2 or 3 of us, 2 paladins, a ranger, and a cleric being the group.  If there's all of us there, it's pretty crap xp, but me + any other 2 are usually able to pull all the stuff before the drop, then the xp is pretty good.  If anyone has a way to single spawns 7 and 8 at 56 that doesn't involve some crazy pet multi-tanking tactics (I'm too old for that nonsense), I'd love to hear it.<br>
